english:
  title: Waiting for the Moon with Longing
  author: Lee Jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Shimmer and shimmer—the moon on the high tower.
    Round and round within the jade window.
    One beauty, lovely and fair,
    Dim and distant beyond autumn's trees.
    I cannot see the perfumed pendant she wears,
    Yet the orchid's fragrance lingers still.
    My yearning—where does it gaze?
    My heart breaks too, reaching toward the edge of sky.
  footnotes:
    - The 'perfumed pendant' (佩) is a traditional ornament worn by noble women, here representing the beloved's presence and beauty.
    - The orchid (蘭) symbolizes purity and noble virtue in East Asian poetry, and its lingering fragrance represents an absent beloved.
